items.sentence: Neither Tom nor Mary has been living here very long.
Neither Tom nor Mary has been going to night school.
Neither Tom nor Mary has been given a second chance.
Tom asked Mary to ask John why he needed to do that.
I told Tom why I'd never graduated from high school.
I didn't want to work with Tom, but I had no choice.
I asked Tom if he'd like to do that on October 20th.
I really don't think Tom did that, but maybe he did.
Mary went to the beauty parlor to get her hair dyed.
Mary was an attractive girl when she was a teenager.
